  {"a":"zilean_sup","b":"alistar","win":["Zilean","Skill","Alistar","Alistar","Alistar","Alistar","Skill"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 2","text":"You both hit level 2 wanting the same window: you want double Q bombs to zone, Alistar wants W-Q to combo your ADC. If you keep vision and hold a Q for the flank you can bomb-and-Speed-Up your carry out before his headbutt lands, keeping the level 2 even."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"Alistar 6 is a nightmare for you: Unbreakable Will makes him nearly unkillable through your poke, so he can W-Q dive under tower and facetank while your bombs tick. Your ult only revives one target and does nothing to stop the initial CC chain, so respect his all-in windows hard."},{"when":"1st item","text":"With his first item Alistar's combo damage and tankiness both jump, and a landed W-Q means guaranteed follow-up your Rewind speed can't fully save. Track his flash and only commit when it's down."},{"when":"Late","text":"Late, your global ult presence, double Speed Up, and AoE zone control let you enable picks across the map where Alistar's short-range engage matters less, evening the matchup back out."}],"wants":{"you":["Keep max distance and poke with double Q from behind minions","Hold Rewind/Speed Up to peel your ADC out of W-Q range","Ward the flanks so his Headbutt-Pulverize can't catch you unseen"],"foe":["Land W (Headbutt) into Q (Pulverize) to lock your carry","All-in at 6 under Unbreakable Will to facetank your poke","Flash-engage to close his short range before you bomb him"]},"early":"Level 1 favours you: your Q bomb outranges everything Alistar has and he has no way to punish you before he gets W-Q online, so you can chip him and deny his cow farm. At level 2 it evens out as he unlocks the W-Q combo threat and you must respect the engage timing rather than poke freely.","mid":"From 3 onward Alistar takes over the lane: every time his Headbutt-Pulverize is up he threatens to knock your ADC into a killable state, and your kit has no hard disengage to stop the initial CC, only a speed buff after the fact. Ward both flanks, hold Speed Up for the peel, and never walk up to bomb him while his W is available.","late":"His level-6 Unbreakable Will and first item make him an unkillable engage tool who can dive your backline and facetank your bombs, so you play purely reactive. Only past two items does it flatten out, where your global ult, AoE zone, and double Speed Up let you dictate picks and objectives that his short range can't reach.","whys":["Level 1 you win because your Q bomb outranges every tool Alistar has before his combo comes online.","Level 2 is even as he unlocks the W-Q engage threat and you must respect it rather than free-poke.","Level 3 Alistar leads because his Headbutt-Pulverize combo can lock your ADC and you can't hard-stop the CC.","Levels 4-5 stay his as repeated W-Q windows outweigh your poke and your speed buff only reacts after the catch.","Level 6 is Alistar's: Unbreakable Will lets him dive and facetank your bombs while chaining CC.","First item keeps him ahead as added tankiness and combo damage make his all-ins nearly unpunishable.","With 2+ items it evens back out as your global ult and double Speed Up enable map-wide picks his short range can't."]},
  {"a":"zilean_sup","b":"bard","win":["Skill","Skill","Skill","Skill","Skill","Skill","Zilean"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 2","text":"Both of you are ranged pokers at 2: your Q bomb versus his Cosmic Binding stun. Whoever lands their skillshot first wins the trade, so use minions to body-block his Q and only bomb when he's committed to a step. It's a clean skill check both ways."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"Bard's Tempered Fate is the swingiest tool in the matchup, able to stasis your ADC mid-combo or set up a pick, while your ult revives one ally after the fact. Track when his ult is up and spread out so a single R can't catch two of you; hold your own R to un-do the damage his roam-pick creates."},{"when":"1st item","text":"Neither of you spikes hard on one item here; the lane stays a poke-and-position duel decided by who lands Q. Your bomb waveclear and his Meep stacks trade roughly even into first back."},{"when":"Late","text":"Late the matchup tips to you: Bard roams and his impact scales down in a set 2v2, while your global ult, double Speed Up, and AoE zone let you save carries through his picks and enable teamfights he can only disrupt."}],"wants":{"you":["Body-block his Cosmic Binding with minions and poke on the whiff","Save Speed Up to walk your ADC out of a landed Q stun","Ward his roam paths and jungle so his Magical Journey ganks don't surprise you"],"foe":["Land Q into a wall or a second body for the long stun","Roam with Magical Journey and Meep-poke while you're pinned to lane","Set up picks with Tempered Fate stasis before you can react"]},"early":"Levels 1-2 are a pure skillshot mirror: your Q bomb and his Cosmic Binding are both delayed poke that miss into good minion positioning, so the trades come down to mechanics and neither of you holds a structural edge. Use the caster minions to block his Q and punish him when he steps up to stack Meeps.","mid":"Through 3 to 6 it stays even and skill-decided. Bard threatens to roam with Magical Journey and pick with a walled stun, but your bomb waveclear lets you match his shove-and-roam and your Speed Up peels his catches. Respect his ult timers and keep vision on his flanks, and the lane never runs away from you.","late":"Once ults and items come online the edge slides to you. In a static 2v2 Bard's roaming value shrinks, and your global Chronoshift, double Speed Up, and AoE bomb zone let you undo his picks and enable fights, so past two items you out-teamfight and out-enable him.","whys":["Level 1 is even: your bomb and his Cosmic Binding are mirrored delayed poke decided by positioning.","Level 2 stays a skill check as both of you gain a second ability but neither gains a structural edge.","Level 3 remains even with waveclear and poke trading roughly one-for-one.","Levels 4-5 are skill-decided as his roam threat is offset by your ability to match and peel.","Level 6 is even: his Tempered Fate pick potential is balanced by your revive undoing the damage.","First item holds even as neither support spikes hard and the lane stays a positioning duel.","With 2+ items you pull ahead as your global ult and double Speed Up out-scale his shrinking roam value."]},
  {"a":"zilean_sup","b":"blitzcrank","win":["Skill","Skill","Skill","Skill","Blitzcrank","Blitzcrank","Zilean"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 2","text":"Level 2 is a standoff: Blitzcrank wants Rocket Grab plus Power Fist to hook-and-pop your ADC, you want double Q to zone. Stand behind your caster minions so a Grab eats a creep, and the lane stays even because one missed hook lets you bomb him for free."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"Blitz spikes here: a landed Rocket Grab into Power Fist and Static Field can delete your ADC before you react, and your ult only revives after the kill, not stopping the pull. Never facecheck a bush and pre-emptively body-block, because his all-in around a hook is lethal at this point."},{"when":"1st item","text":"With his first item Blitz's Q burst and knock-up chain hit hard enough that a single hook trades a life, so the pressure of his cooldown dominates lane state. Ward both bushes and hold Speed Up to yank your carry out of Grab range on the whiff."},{"when":"Late","text":"Late you take over: once his Grab is warded and his one-shot pick is answered by your Chronoshift, your global ult, double Speed Up and AoE zone let you play around his cooldown and win the sustained fights his single-target catch can't."}],"wants":{"you":["Stand behind minions so a Rocket Grab hits a creep, not your carry","Ward both lane bushes to remove hook fog","Hold Speed Up and Chronoshift to answer a landed Grab all-in"],"foe":["Land Rocket Grab into Power Fist to isolate and burst your ADC","Fish hooks from fog and all-in when yours is out of position","Use the level 6 Static Field burst to finish a hooked target"]},"early":"Levels 1-4 are a skillshot standoff decided by hook discipline. Blitzcrank's Rocket Grab is his entire threat, and if you sit behind your caster minions and keep the bushes warded, a missed hook hands you a free bomb window. Your double Q zones him off the wave, so as long as you don't get caught the early lane holds even.","mid":"The matchup peaks in his favour at 6. A landed Grab into Power Fist and Static Field can burst your ADC out before your Rewind or Speed Up matters, and your ult only brings the target back after the pull, not preventing it. This stays his lane through first item, where the sheer punish of one hook dominates, so you play safe, ward aggressively, and never step into fog.","late":"Once you can trade Chronoshift for his hook, the matchup flips to you. His catch is single-target and cooldown-reliant, while your global ult, double Speed Up, and AoE bomb zone win extended fights and let your team play around a whiffed Grab, so past two items Zilean out-scales him.","whys":["Level 1 is even: Blitz's only threat is a hook you can body-block behind minions.","Level 2 stays a standoff as good positioning nullifies Grab and lets you free-poke on a miss.","Level 3 remains even with hook discipline keeping the lane a skill check.","Levels 4-5 hold even as warded bushes deny his fog hooks and your zone controls the wave.","Level 6 is Blitzcrank's: Grab into Power Fist and Static Field can burst your carry before you react.","First item keeps him ahead as his hook-all-in trades a full life and your revive only answers after.","With 2+ items you win as Chronoshift and double Speed Up let you play around his single-target catch."]},
  {"a":"zilean_sup","b":"brand","win":["Skill","Skill","Brand","Brand","Brand","Brand","Zilean"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 2","text":"Level 2 is a poke mirror: your double Q versus his Pillar of Flame into Sear stun combo. Brand's damage is higher but needs the stun to land, so if you sidestep his Q-into-W setup you can bomb him even. Body-block his skillshots with minions and it stays a skill check."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"Brand spikes hard from 3 on and 6 only widens it: Pyroclasm bounces for huge AoE and his passive burn out-damages your poke in every extended trade. Your ult revives one ally but does nothing about his relentless chip, so avoid long fights and use Speed Up to break line of sight after his combo."},{"when":"1st item","text":"With his first item Brand's burst crosses the threshold where a full Q-W-E combo can nearly kill your ADC through your heals-free kit, dominating lane. Keep your carry behind minions, dodge Sear, and only trade when his Pillar of Flame is on cooldown."},{"when":"Late","text":"Late the matchup swings to you: teamfights favour your Chronoshift on a fed carry, double Speed Up engage/disengage, and AoE zone, letting you negate Brand's burst-them-down plan by reviving his priority kill and speeding your team through his combo."}],"wants":{"you":["Sidestep Sear so his stun never lands and his combo falls apart","Break line of sight with Speed Up after he commits Pillar of Flame","Keep your ADC behind minions to eat Pyroclasm bounces on creeps"],"foe":["Land Pillar of Flame into Sear for the stun-into-burst combo","Stack passive burn in extended trades to out-damage your poke","Ult Pyroclasm into a grouped 2v2 to bounce for massive AoE"]},"early":"Levels 1-2 are an even poke duel. Your double Q bomb matches his Pillar of Flame in range, and because Brand needs to land Sear for his real damage, disciplined dodging behind minions keeps the trades one-for-one. Punish him whenever his Q is down and don't let him free-stack his passive on you.","mid":"From level 3 Brand takes the lane. His Q-W-E combo and passive burn out-damage your bombs in every extended exchange, and Zilean has no heal or shield to sustain through it, so you're forced to concede poke. This stays his through 6 and first item, where a landed combo threatens to kill your ADC outright; play to dodge, break sightlines with Speed Up, and never sit in a prolonged trade.","late":"Once fights become 5v5 or objective 2v2s, the value flips to you. Chronoshift undoes the kill his whole kit is built to score, double Speed Up lets your team close or escape his combo, and your AoE zone controls chokes, so past two items Zilean's utility outweighs Brand's burst.","whys":["Level 1 is even: your bomb matches his Pillar of Flame range and he needs a stun to threaten you.","Level 2 stays a skill check as dodging Sear keeps his combo trades one-for-one.","Level 3 Brand leads as his Q-W-E combo and burn out-damage your poke with no sustain to answer.","Levels 4-5 stay his: repeated combos and passive stacking win every extended trade.","Level 6 is Brand's as Pyroclasm adds huge AoE burst your revive can't pre-empt.","First item keeps him ahead when a full combo can nearly kill your carry outright.","With 2+ items you win as Chronoshift and double Speed Up negate his burst-them-down teamfight plan."]},
  {"a":"zilean_sup","b":"braum","win":["Zilean","Zilean","Skill","Skill","Skill","Skill","Zilean"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 2","text":"You own level 2: your double Q bomb pokes Braum freely while his only real engage is a telegraphed Winter's Bite slow at short range that you can Rewind-Speed away from. He can't threaten a kill this early, so you chip his health and shove for the level advantage."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"Braum's Glacial Fissure adds a knock-up-and-slow zone, but it's a slow engage you can see coming, and your ult revives through his all-in while Speed Up pulls your ADC out of the Concussive Blows stun setup. It's roughly even at 6: he peels well, you disengage well."},{"when":"1st item","text":"With first items Braum becomes a sturdier peel wall but his kill threat stays low, so the lane stays even and grindy. Keep bombing him and his ADC through his shields; your poke tempo out-values his passive stun over a long lane."},{"when":"Late","text":"Late you edge ahead again: your Chronoshift on a carry beats his single-target peel, and double Speed Up plus AoE zone let your team dictate fights his stationary Fissure and shield can only react to."}],"wants":{"you":["Poke with double Q from range where Winter's Bite can't reach","Save Speed Up to break the Concussive Blows stun setup","Keep tempo pokes on his ADC through Braum's Unbreakable shield"],"foe":["Land Winter's Bite to start the Concussive Blows stun stack","Wall your ADC with Unbreakable to negate your bombs","Zone with Glacial Fissure to peel and slow your all-in"]},"early":"Levels 1-2 are firmly yours. Braum's engage is a short-range Winter's Bite slow, and before he can chain Concussive Blows he has no burst, so your double Q bomb out-ranges and out-tempos him. Chip him and his ADC, shove the wave, and take the early lead while his kit is purely defensive.","mid":"From 3 onward it settles into an even grind. Braum's Unbreakable shield blocks your bombs and his passive threatens a stun if he lands Bite, but you can Rewind-Speed out of the stun setup and keep poking. Neither of you has the kill pressure to break the other, so it's a skill-decided farm lane through 6.","late":"The scaling tips back to you. Your global Chronoshift outvalues his single-target peel, and double Speed Up plus your AoE bomb zone let your team choose fights, while Braum's stationary Glacial Fissure and shield can only react. Past two items Zilean's tempo and utility win out.","whys":["Level 1 you win: your bomb out-ranges Braum's short Winter's Bite and he has zero burst.","Level 2 stays yours as double Q out-tempos his defensive kit before Concussive Blows comes online.","Level 3 evens out once his shield and passive stun threat let him hold his ground.","Levels 4-5 are skill-decided as his peel offsets your poke in a grindy farm lane.","Level 6 is even: his Glacial Fissure peel is matched by your revive and Speed Up disengage.","First item stays even as sturdier Braum still lacks kill pressure against your poke.","With 2+ items you edge ahead as Chronoshift and double Speed Up outscale his single-target peel."]},
  {"a":"zilean_sup","b":"galio","win":["Zilean","Zilean","Skill","Skill","Galio","Skill","Zilean"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 2","text":"You dominate level 2: your double Q bomb out-ranges Galio's slow Winds of War and he has no reliable engage before Justice Punch is online. Chip him while he's forced to eat poke to farm, and shove for prio; he simply can't fight back at this point."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"Galio 6 is the danger spike: Hero's Entrance is a global engage that flies onto your ADC with knock-up and taunt, and it can be timed with a roaming ally. Your ult only revives after the dive, so ward wide, respect his ult being up, and hold Speed Up to reposition before the landing pops."},{"when":"1st item","text":"Just after his ult window the lane settles even again: his one-shot engage is on cooldown and your poke resumes, so a Chronoshift held for his next Entrance neutralizes his main threat. Trade freely while his R and Justice Punch are down."},{"when":"Late","text":"Late you pull ahead: your global Chronoshift, double Speed Up, and AoE zone let your team play around Galio's telegraphed engage, reviving his taunt target and speeding out of his combo so his single commitment wins nothing."}],"wants":{"you":["Poke with double Q from max range where Winds of War can't reach","Ward wide and track Galio's ult so Hero's Entrance can't surprise you","Hold Chronoshift and Speed Up to answer his Justice Punch taunt dive"],"foe":["Land Winds of War into Justice Punch to taunt and combo your carry","Use Hero's Entrance to global-engage onto your backline with a roamer","Charge W to shield and tank your bombs during the all-in"]},"early":"Levels 1-2 belong to you. Galio's Winds of War is slow and short compared to your double Q bomb, and without Justice Punch he can't punish you, so you free-poke him off the wave and take an early health and prio lead while he's stuck farming under pressure.","mid":"From 3 to 5 it evens as Galio unlocks Justice Punch and his W shield, letting him charge tankiness and threaten a taunt-combo if he closes distance. You still hold poke range, but you must respect the gap-close, so trades become a skill check around dodging his Q-E setup and not overextending.","late":"Level 6 is his spike, where Hero's Entrance turns him into a global dive that can knock up and taunt your ADC from off-screen, so you ward wide and hold your revive. But right after and into two items the edge returns to you: your Chronoshift undoes his taunt-kill, double Speed Up repositions your team out of his combo, and your AoE zone controls the fight his single telegraphed engage can't win.","whys":["Level 1 you win: your bomb out-ranges Galio's slow Winds of War and he has no engage.","Level 2 stays yours as double Q keeps him eating poke before Justice Punch comes online.","Level 3 evens out once Justice Punch and his W shield give him a gap-close and tankiness.","Levels 4-5 are a skill check around dodging his Q-E taunt setup as he charges durability.","Level 6 is Galio's: Hero's Entrance is a global knock-up-and-taunt dive onto your carry.","First item swings back even as his ult goes on cooldown and your poke resumes with a revive held.","With 2+ items you win as Chronoshift and double Speed Up let your team play around his telegraphed engage."]},
  {"a":"zilean_sup","b":"hwei","win":["Skill","Skill","Hwei","Hwei","Hwei","Hwei","Zilean"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 2","text":"You both hit Lvl 2 wanting the same window: your double-Bomb (E-Q or two Q ticks) can chunk him, but Hwei's QQ pool zone plus QW disdain out-ranges you, so respect his casting distance and don't walk into the AoE for a single Bomb."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"Chronoshift flips his all-in math, but Hwei's ult picks the trade angle he wants and his QE Devastating Fire deletes minions to zone you off XP; his kill pressure through mid-game is real even with your revive banked."},{"when":"1st item","text":"With a Rod component your Bomb-slow chains threaten more, but Hwei still out-pokes on raw range; use E slow to help your ADC dodge his QE detonation rather than trading autos."},{"when":"Late","text":"Two items in, your Chronoshift plus double Time Warp swing extended fights your way: peel your carry off his EE trap and QW, then rewind a dead ally to nullify his best combo."}],"wants":{"you":["Land Time Bomb (Q) off a minion or Rewind reset to double-detonate the moment he steps up","Bank Chronoshift on your ADC before he commits his Q pool combo","Stretch fights past his cooldowns where your revive and speed outlast his mana"],"foe":["Poke you and your ADC from max range with QQ and QE before you close distance","Zone your carry off CS with Devastating Fire minion clear","Catch a Bomb-less window to land his EE root and follow with disdain"]},"early":"Levels 1-2 are close and skill-dependent: you can trade with a double Time Bomb but Hwei's pool poke and range mean neither of you dominates, so play for XP and safe Bomb throws.","mid":"Levels 3-6 tilt to Hwei. His full QWE kit out-ranges your single-target Bomb, his QE shreds your wave and health bar, and even Chronoshift at 6 doesn't stop him dictating trades from distance.","late":"Once you hit items and two Time Warps, you flip the extended-fight math: Chronoshift and double slows let you peel his combo and outlast his mana in drawn-out 2v2s and teamfights.","whys":["Level 1 is even because both of you are poking safely with no engage tools online yet.","Level 2 stays skill-based: your double-Bomb spike answers his early pool poke evenly.","Level 3 favors Hwei as his full Q pool and QE range out-trade your single Bomb.","Levels 4-5 favor Hwei because his Devastating Fire zones your carry off XP and CS.","Level 6 favors Hwei since his ult picks the fight angle and out-ranges your revive-based all-in.","At first item Hwei still out-pokes you on raw range before your scaling comes online.","At two-plus items you win: Chronoshift and double Time Warp outlast his combo in long fights."]},
  {"a":"zilean_sup","b":"janna","win":["Zilean","Zilean","Zilean","Zilean","Skill","Skill","Skill"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 2","text":"You spike hard at 2: double Time Bomb off a Rewind reset can burst Janna, who has no sustain and a flimsy body, so pair a Bomb with your ADC's auto commitment to force a summoner or a kill."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"Chronoshift arrives, but so does Monsoon: her ult knocks you off and heals her ADC, cancelling your all-in and buying disengage, so the level-6 window neutralizes your early lead."},{"when":"1st item","text":"Both of you come online as enablers; your Bomb chains still poke, but Janna's Q shield and W slow start covering her ADC well enough that trades even out."},{"when":"Late","text":"Two utility supports scaling: it becomes a peel war where your Chronoshift and speeds trade against her shields, Monsoon disengage, and Eye of the Storm, decided by execution not kit."}],"wants":{"you":["Open every trade with a double Bomb burst before her Q shield refreshes","Use Time Warp to catch her out of position for your ADC to collapse","Punish her weak early body in the levels 1-4 all-in window"],"foe":["Shield the incoming Bomb detonation with Eye of the Storm on her carry","Bank Monsoon to knock you back the instant you commit Chronoshift","Slow-peel with tornado and W to stall until her ADC scales"]},"early":"Levels 1-4 are yours: Janna has no sustain and a fragile body, so your double Time Bomb burst plus Rewind resets let you win the poke war and threaten a real all-in with your ADC before she has shields to spare.","mid":"Around level 6 the lane evens out. Chronoshift is strong, but Monsoon hard-counters your commit by knocking you off and healing, so your early pressure stops snowballing.","late":"Late game is a skill-decided peel duel: your revive and double slows against her shields, Eye of the Storm, and Monsoon disengage, won by who executes their utility cleaner in fights.","whys":["Level 1 favors you: Janna's fragile no-sustain body loses the early poke exchange to your Bomb.","Level 2 favors you as your double-Bomb spike threatens a kill she can't heal through.","Level 3 stays yours because your Bomb pressure keeps her ADC and her low-HP body honest.","Levels 4-5 remain yours: her shields alone can't cover the all-in window you create.","Level 6 evens out because Monsoon knocks you off your Chronoshift commit and disengages.","At first item both come online as enablers and her shield uptime neutralizes your poke.","At two-plus items it's a skill-based peel war between two utility supports."]},
  {"a":"zilean_sup","b":"karma","win":["Karma","Karma","Karma","Karma","Skill","Skill","Zilean"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 2","text":"Karma out-trades you early: her Q Inner Flame is a wide poke that out-ranges your single Time Bomb, and RQ empowered detonation zones you hard, so avoid stepping up for one Bomb into her mana-free harass."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"You get Chronoshift but Karma has had her R since level 1, so she's been enabling all game; her empowered Q burst plus mantra shield still lets her win poke and cover an all-in better than your revive alone."},{"when":"1st item","text":"The gap starts closing as your Bomb slows chain with items; her mantra empowerment on cooldown gives you windows, so trade when RQ is down, not when it's up."},{"when":"Late","text":"Two items and double Time Warp swing extended fights your way: Chronoshift plus speed out-sustains her poke, and you peel her RE shield-speed engage off your carry."}],"wants":{"you":["Trade only when her Mantra (RQ) is on cooldown","Chain Bomb slows to help your ADC dodge her empowered Q","Drag fights long so your revive and speed outlast her mana poke"],"foe":["Poke with wide Inner Flame and RQ before you can close range","Use RE shield and haste to disengage your all-in or speed her carry away","Zone your ADC off CS with empowered Q AoE"]},"early":"Levels 1-4 belong to Karma. Her Mantra is online from level 1, so her RQ Inner Flame out-ranges and out-damages your single Time Bomb, and she harasses mana-free while you can't safely step up to detonate.","mid":"By level 6 it evens: you finally have Chronoshift to answer her engage, and her Mantra windows give you openings to trade when RQ is on cooldown rather than eating it.","late":"Two items in, you take over. Double Time Warp and Chronoshift out-sustain her poke in long fights, and your slows plus revive let you peel her RE engage off your carry.","whys":["Level 1 favors Karma: her Mantra-empowered Q out-ranges your single Bomb from the first minute.","Level 2 favors Karma as her mana-free RQ poke beats your step-up Bomb trade.","Level 3 stays Karma's with empowered Q zoning your carry off farm.","Levels 4-5 favor Karma because her Mantra uptime keeps out-poking your kit.","Level 6 evens out once Chronoshift gives you an answer to her engage and burst.","At first item it's skill-based: her Mantra cooldowns open windows your slows can punish.","At two-plus items you win: double Time Warp and revive outlast her poke and peel her engage."]},
  {"a":"zilean_sup","b":"leona","win":["Skill","Leona","Leona","Leona","Leona","Leona","Zilean"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 2","text":"Leona spikes brutally at 2: her E Zenith Blade engage plus Q stun is a guaranteed CC chain your Bomb can't interrupt, so hold your Time Warp on your ADC to speed them out the instant she dashes."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"Solar Flare gives her a second hard-CC layer to chain onto E-Q-passive; Chronoshift can bait her whole combo, but if she times R after your revive she still kills through it, so respect the double-engage."},{"when":"1st item","text":"With CDR and a Rod your Bomb speed-slows help your carry survive her engage, but Leona still dictates when fights start; ward her engage flanks and pre-speed before she reaches you."},{"when":"Late","text":"Two items and double Time Warp flip it: her all-in is single-target, so Chronoshift plus proactive speeds let you save the pick target and win the ensuing 2v2 once her combo is spent."}],"wants":{"you":["Pre-cast Time Warp on your ADC to escape her E engage range","Bank Chronoshift to bait and waste her full CC chain","Ward the flanks so her Zenith Blade never lands unseen"],"foe":["Land E Zenith Blade to lock the CC chain onto your carry","Stack Solar Flare onto E-Q for an unbreakable stun window","Force the all-in before your speeds and revive are up"]},"early":"Level 1 is even before her engage is online, but from level 2 Leona owns the lane: E-Q is point-and-click hard CC your Bomb can't stop, and one clean engage onto your ADC snowballs the 2v2.","mid":"Levels 3-6 stay Leona's. Her CC chain plus Solar Flare gives two hard-engage layers, and even Chronoshift only baits one combo; she decides every fight's timing while you play reactive.","late":"Two items in you take over: her all-in is single-target, so double Time Warp and Chronoshift let you pre-speed the target out or revive through it, then win the drawn-out 2v2.","whys":["Level 1 is even since Leona's engage isn't online and neither of you can commit yet.","Level 2 favors Leona: E-Q point-and-click CC chains onto your carry uninterrupted.","Level 3 stays Leona's as her engage keeps dictating every trade.","Levels 4-5 favor Leona with her CC lock still out-threatening your reactive kit.","Level 6 favors Leona because Solar Flare adds a second unbreakable CC layer.","At first item Leona still controls fight timing despite your speed-slows.","At two-plus items you win: double Time Warp and revive save her single-target pick and outlast her combo."]},
  {"a":"zilean_sup","b":"lulu","win":["Lulu","Lulu","Lulu","Skill","Skill","Skill","Skill"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 2","text":"Lulu wins the early poke: her Q Glitterlance out-ranges your single Time Bomb and slows you, and her E on her ADC adds free harass, so don't step up to detonate into her Q slow zone."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"You get Chronoshift, but Lulu's Wild Growth is the better all-in answer, knocking up your engage and shielding a huge health buffer; her Polymorph also cancels your Bomb-detonation follow-up, so trades stay in her favor."},{"when":"1st item","text":"The lane levels off as both scale into enablers; your Bomb speed-slows create pick windows when her W Polymorph and E shield are on cooldown, so bait those before committing."},{"when":"Late","text":"Two peel supports in a skill duel: your Chronoshift plus double Time Warp trade against her shield, Polymorph, and knockup ult, decided by who lands their utility first."}],"wants":{"you":["Commit only when her Polymorph (W) is on cooldown","Use Bomb slows to set up a pick her shield can't fully cover","Speed your ADC in and out around her poke with Time Warp"],"foe":["Poke you down with Glitterlance and E harass before you close","Polymorph you mid-combo to cancel your Bomb detonation","Save Wild Growth to knock up and shield-buffer your all-in"]},"early":"Levels 1-3 favor Lulu. Her Glitterlance out-ranges your single Bomb and slows, her E gives free poke through her ADC, and Polymorph threatens to cancel your combo, so you play safe and farm XP.","mid":"By level 4 it evens. Chronoshift and your slows create pick windows, but you must respect Wild Growth and Polymorph; trade only when her key cooldowns are down.","late":"Late game is a skill-decided peel duel: your revive and double Time Warp against her shields, Polymorph, and knockup ult, won by whoever lands their utility cleaner in the fight.","whys":["Level 1 favors Lulu: Glitterlance out-ranges your Bomb and adds a slow you can't answer.","Level 2 favors Lulu as her Q plus E poke beats your single-target step-up.","Level 3 stays Lulu's with Polymorph threatening to cancel your detonation combo.","Levels 4-5 even out once Chronoshift and your slows open pick windows.","Level 6 is skill-based: your revive trades against her Wild Growth knockup and shield.","At first item both are online enablers and her cooldown gaps decide the trades.","At two-plus items it's an even peel duel between two utility supports."]},
  {"a":"zilean_sup","b":"lux","win":["Lux","Lux","Lux","Lux","Lux","Lux","Zilean"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 2","text":"Lux out-pokes and out-threatens you: her Q Light Binding is a long-range root that sets up her E and your ADC's collapse, and it out-ranges your single Time Bomb, so hug minions and never walk in a straight line."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"Final Spark is a lane-wide execute that punishes your poke health bars; Chronoshift can bait it, but a good Lux waits out your revive, so her burst combo still dictates kills through mid-game."},{"when":"1st item","text":"With a Rod, Lux's Q-E-R combo does even more, and her range keeps you reactive; use Bomb slows purely to help your carry dodge her Light Binding, not to trade autos."},{"when":"Late","text":"Two items and double Time Warp finally flip it: her all-in hinges on landing Q, so Chronoshift plus proactive speeds let you dodge or revive through the combo and win the drawn-out fight."}],"wants":{"you":["Break line of sight and hug minions so her Q Light Binding whiffs","Bank Chronoshift to bait Final Spark, then win the follow-up","Use Bomb slows to help your ADC sidestep her root and E"],"foe":["Land Light Binding to chain E and burst with your carry","Poke your health bars low for a Final Spark execute window","Keep max range so you stay reactive to her skillshots"]},"early":"Levels 1-5 belong to Lux. Her Light Binding root out-ranges your single Bomb and sets up burst, her E adds AoE poke, and she keeps you reactive; one landed Q onto your ADC can end the trade.","mid":"Level 6 stays Lux's: Final Spark executes your poked-down health bars from a screen away, and even Chronoshift only baits one combo before she waits out your revive.","late":"Two items in you take over. Her entire threat hinges on landing Q, so double Time Warp and Chronoshift let you dodge or revive through it, then outlast her spent combo in the 2v2.","whys":["Level 1 favors Lux: her long-range Q root out-threatens your single-target Bomb.","Level 2 favors Lux as Light Binding sets up burst your kit can't answer.","Level 3 stays Lux's with Q-E poke keeping you reactive and low.","Levels 4-5 favor Lux because her range and root control every trade.","Level 6 favors Lux since Final Spark executes your poked health bars from afar.","At first item Lux's amplified combo and range still keep you on the back foot.","At two-plus items you win: double Time Warp and revive dodge or nullify her landed-Q combo."]},
  {"a":"zilean_sup","b":"maokai","win":["Skill","Skill","Maokai","Maokai","Maokai","Skill","Zilean"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 2","text":"Both of you are hunting the same spike: if you hit 2 first you can Q the enemy ADC through Maokai and burst them, but Maokai's Sapling Toss (E) zones your walk-up so the level-2 all-in is a coinflip that comes down to who steps first."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"Maokai's Nature's Grasp (R) is a lane-wide root that turns any of his saplings or a Twisted Advance (W) into a kill; you can't cleanse it, so respect his 6 and hold your own Chronoshift as an insurance policy rather than trading into his engage window."},{"when":"1st item","text":"Once you finish your first component and pick up mana sustain, your double-bomb poke and reliable Time Warp (E) peel start dragging the lane back — Maokai's kit has no ranged execute, so you outlast his sapling chip."},{"when":"Late","text":"Chronoshift plus your speed-ups makes you the premier peeler versus a Maokai dive; you rez your carry through his W-root all-in and his single-target lockdown wastes itself, tilting teamfights your way."}],"wants":{"you":["Space so Maokai's W (Twisted Advance) whiffs and can't chain into his root","Bomb the ADC when Maokai steps up to place a sapling","Hold Chronoshift for the target his R+W is diving"],"foe":["Land Sapling Toss (E) on your face to force a bad walk-up","Twisted Advance (W) onto your ADC then Nature's Grasp (R) follow-up","Trade sustain-heavy so his passive sapling regen wins the poke war"]},"early":"Levels 1-2 are even and skill-based — you both want the same level-2 timing, and it comes down to who dodges the other's opener. Bomb the ADC when Maokai walks up to sapling, and don't stand on placed saplings or you feed his slow.","mid":"Levels 3-5 tip to Maokai: his Sapling Toss zoning plus Twisted Advance gives him a real gank-setup and pick threat that your immobile body can't cleanly answer, and his passive sustain lets him win the sapling-chip war. Play back, use E on your ADC to reposition out of his W range, and ward the flanks his R can start from.","late":"By first item and especially two items the matchup flips to you: mana sustain fuels your double-bomb poke, and Chronoshift plus double speed-ups make his single-target lockdown a non-threat in fights — you rez through his all-in and peel his dive apart.","whys":["Level 1 is even — neither support pressures the other before abilities come online.","Level 2 is a skill coinflip; both want the same spike and it's decided by who commits first.","Level 3 favours Maokai as his Sapling zoning and W pick threat outmuscle your walk-up.","Levels 4-5 stay Maokai's as his sustain and engage setup dominate the immobile lane.","Level 6 favours Maokai — his lane-wide Nature's Grasp root converts any sapling or W into a kill.","First item is even as your mana sustain and poke start neutralizing his sapling chip.","At two-plus items you pull ahead — Chronoshift and speed peel shred his single-target dive."]},
  {"a":"zilean_sup","b":"milio","win":["Skill","Skill","Skill","Skill","Skill","Skill","Skill"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 2","text":"Neither of you engages at 2 — Milio wants Fired Up! (Q) plus Warm Hugs (W) to zone and sustain, you want Time Bomb plus Rewind for double-poke, so the level-2 spike is a poke exchange, not an all-in, and it's even."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"Milio's Breath of Life (R) cleanses your slows and heals his backline, directly countering your Time Bomb burst; you answer with Chronoshift, so the ult war is a mirror of insurance tools and stays even."},{"when":"1st item","text":"Both of you are enchanters buying the same sustain items — your double-bomb poke versus his shielding and cleanse trade evenly, and neither support snowballs the 2v2 alone."},{"when":"Late","text":"Milio's ult ungroups your CC and his passive gives his ADC range; Chronoshift and your speed-ups keep your carry alive through his poke. It's a peel-versus-peel standoff decided by the carries, not the supports."}],"wants":{"you":["Chain Time Bomb into Rewind for a double-bomb poke before his shields land","Speed your ADC in and out of Milio's Warm Hugs (W) slow range","Bait his Breath of Life (R) cleanse before committing hard CC"],"foe":["Pre-shield the ADC with Warm Hugs (W) to eat your bomb damage","Cleanse your Time Bomb slow with Breath of Life (R) at the right moment","Extend his ADC's range with Fired Up! passive to out-trade in poke"]},"early":"Levels 1-2 are a pure skill exchange — two enchanters trading spells with no hard engage. Land your double-bomb before Milio pre-shields, and use your speed to reposition your ADC out of his Warm Hugs slow.","mid":"Levels 3-6 stay even. Milio's shielding and cleanse blunt your poke while your Time Warp mobility keeps your carry safe from his; whoever's ADC lands more auto trades pulls ahead, not the supports. Ward river for both junglers since neither of you can hard-set a gank alone.","late":"With items it remains a peel-versus-peel mirror: his Breath of Life ungroups your slows, your Chronoshift denies his all-in a kill. The matchup is genuinely coinflip and comes down to carry execution and macro, so focus on flawless bomb-peel and vision.","whys":["Level 1 is even — two enchanters with no engage trade spells on equal footing.","Level 2 stays skill-based; both spike into poke/sustain, not an all-in.","Level 3 is even as his shields answer your bombs blow for blow.","Levels 4-5 remain a coinflip decided by ADC trades, not support edges.","Level 6 is even — his Breath of Life and your Chronoshift are mirrored insurance ults.","First item is even; identical enchanter itemization keeps neither ahead.","Two-plus items stays even — peel-versus-peel standoff decided by the carries."]},
  {"a":"zilean_sup","b":"morgana","win":["Skill","Skill","Skill","Skill","Skill","Skill","Zilean"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 2","text":"Neither of you all-ins at 2 — Morgana wants Q (Dark Binding) plus W (Tormented Shadow) to zone and poke, you want Time Bomb plus Rewind for double-poke, so it's a spell-trading standoff and the level-2 timing is even."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"Morgana's Soul Shackles (R) is a point-blank chain that needs her on top of you; your Chronoshift and speed-ups let you kite the tether or rez through it, so her ult threat is real but answerable and the fight stays even."},{"when":"1st item","text":"Both supports scale on mana and utility; her Black Shield can eat one of your bombs' slow but not both, and your poke keeps pace — first-item trades even out."},{"when":"Late","text":"By two items your kit outclasses hers as a peel tool: Chronoshift denies her Soul Shackles all-in a kill and your speed lets your team walk out of her ult radius, so late-game teamfighting tilts to you."}],"wants":{"you":["Double-bomb with Rewind so one lands even after Black Shield absorbs the other","Speed your ADC sideways to dodge Dark Binding (Q)","Hold Chronoshift to rez through her Soul Shackles (R) all-in"],"foe":["Land Dark Binding (Q) to root you for a full W+ignite trade","Black Shield (E) the ADC to negate your Time Bomb slow before engaging","Flash-R Soul Shackles into your grouped backline"]},"early":"Levels 1-2 are even and skill-based — Morgana's Dark Binding is her whole kill threat, so if you sidestep it with good spacing and your ADC's movement, she has no follow-up. Trade with double-bombs and don't clump near minions she's W-ing.","mid":"Levels 3-6 stay a coinflip. Her Black Shield is strong: it blocks your bomb slow and a jungler's CC, so bait it before you commit hard. Her only lockdown is a skillshot Q — respect it, ward for a Q-flash gank, and keep peppering with poke since she has no sustain edge on you.","late":"With items you edge ahead: Chronoshift plus double speed-ups make you the better peeler, denying her Soul Shackles all-in the kill it needs and letting your carry stroll out of the tether radius. Play for scaling teamfights where your utility outshines her single pick.","whys":["Level 1 is even — both trade spells with no engage online.","Level 2 stays skill-based; neither support has an all-in yet.","Level 3 is even as her Black Shield answers your poke and her Q is dodgeable.","Levels 4-5 remain a coinflip decided by whether her Dark Binding lands.","Level 6 is even — her Soul Shackles threat is matched by your Chronoshift and speed.","First item is even; her shield and your double-bomb cancel out.","Two-plus items favours you as Chronoshift and speed out-peel her single pick threat."]},
  {"a":"zilean_sup","b":"nami","win":["Nami","Nami","Nami","Skill","Skill","Skill","Skill"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 2","text":"Nami's level-2 is scary: Aqua Prison (Q) bubble plus Ebb and Flow (W) gives her a point-and-click kill combo the moment she hits 2, and your immobile body is a prime bubble target — she wins this timing outright, so play back until you have Rewind for double-bomb answer."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"Nami's Tidal Wave (R) is a wide knock-up that sets her ADC's whole all-in; you answer with Chronoshift and speed-ups to peel or rez, so her 6 is dangerous but you're no longer strictly behind — it evens out."},{"when":"1st item","text":"With mana sustain online your double-bomb poke matches Nami's E-empowered auto trades, and her early bubble dominance fades as your spacing improves — the lane levels off."},{"when":"Late","text":"Both are top-tier enchanters; Chronoshift versus her Tidal Wave engage is a genuine peel mirror, and the teamfight comes down to carries. Neither support wins the late 2v2 alone."}],"wants":{"you":["Space out of Aqua Prison (Q) range — it's her whole kill threat","Bomb the ADC when Nami steps up to E-buff an auto","Hold Chronoshift and speed for her Tidal Wave (R) all-in"],"foe":["Land Aqua Prison (Q) on your stationary body for a free trade","Ebb and Flow (W) bounce poke to win the sustain-trade war","Tidal Wave (R) into the ADC's follow-up burst"]},"early":"Levels 1-3 belong to Nami: her Aqua Prison bubble plus Ebb and Flow is a reliable point-and-click trade that punishes your lack of mobility, and she out-pokes and out-sustains you before your kit comes online. Sit back, dodge bubbles by moving unpredictably, and don't walk up to CS-shove into her level-2 spike.","mid":"Levels 4-6 stabilize to even. Once you have Rewind for double-bombs and some mana sustain, you match her poke and her bubble is easier to space. Respect her Tidal Wave at 6 — it sets her ADC's all-in — but your Chronoshift and Time Warp let you peel the follow-up. Ward for jungle since her Q makes ganks lethal.","late":"With items it's a clean enchanter mirror. Chronoshift denies her Tidal Wave engage the kill it wants, your speed-ups walk your carry out of trouble, and she peels just as well the other way. The 2v2 is decided by ADC execution and macro, not the supports.","whys":["Level 1 favours Nami — her bubble threat pressures your immobile body from the start.","Level 2 is Nami's as her Q+W combo becomes a point-and-click kill trade.","Level 3 stays Nami's; she out-pokes and out-sustains before your kit spikes.","Levels 4-5 even out once Rewind gives you double-bomb answers.","Level 6 is even — her Tidal Wave threat is matched by your Chronoshift peel.","First item is even as mana sustain lets your poke keep pace.","Two-plus items stays even — a peel mirror decided by the carries."]},
  {"a":"zilean_sup","b":"nautilus","win":["Skill","Nautilus","Nautilus","Nautilus","Nautilus","Nautilus","Zilean"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 2","text":"Nautilus spikes hard at 2: Dredge Line (Q) hook plus Titan's Wrath (W) shield lets him hook-engage and eat your bomb through the shield, and you can't dash out — so the level-2 all-in is his. Hold the wave back and don't stand next to walls he can Q off of."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"Depth Charge (R) is an unstoppable homing knock-up that chains with his Q hook and passive root for a full CC lock on your carry; you can't cleanse it, so pre-shield with Chronoshift and speed the target out of his hook range."},{"when":"1st item","text":"Nautilus stays ahead through his item spike — his hook is still a lane-ending threat and his CC chain out-pressures your poke, so keep spacing and ward the walls he engages from."},{"when":"Late","text":"By two items you flip it: Chronoshift plus double speed-ups make you the ideal anti-Nautilus peeler — you rez your carry through his full R-Q-passive chain and speed them out of his hook, wasting his entire kit."}],"wants":{"you":["Stand away from walls so Dredge Line (Q) can't pull you","Speed your ADC out of hook range the instant Nautilus steps up","Save Chronoshift for the target his Depth Charge (R) locks"],"foe":["Land Dredge Line (Q) on you or the ADC to start his CC chain","Titan's Wrath (W) shield to tank your bomb during the all-in","Depth Charge (R) into Q+passive for an inescapable lockdown"]},"early":"Level 1 is even, but from level 2 on Nautilus owns the lane. His Dredge Line hook plus Titan's Wrath shield is a repeatable engage your immobile kit can't dodge or trade back into, and one hook near a wall is a kill. Hug the middle of the lane away from terrain, keep the wave on your side, and only bomb when he's on cooldown.","mid":"Levels 3-6 stay Nautilus-favoured. His CC chain — hook, passive root, W stun — out-pressures your poke, and at 6 Depth Charge sets an unstoppable all-in. Use Time Warp to yank your ADC out of hook range, pre-cast Chronoshift on the dive target, and ward the side walls so his engage doesn't come uncontested.","late":"Two items flips the matchup to you. Chronoshift is the perfect answer to his single-target lockdown — you rez your carry through the full R-Q-passive chain — and your speed-ups walk them clean out of hook threat. His whole kit is CC on one target, and you're the best support in the game at nullifying exactly that.","whys":["Level 1 is even before Nautilus's hook-shield combo comes online.","Level 2 favours Nautilus as Q+W gives him a repeatable engage you can't dodge.","Level 3 stays Nautilus's; his CC chain out-pressures your poke.","Levels 4-5 remain Nautilus-favoured on hook threat and lane control.","Level 6 is Nautilus's — unstoppable Depth Charge sets a full lockdown all-in.","First item keeps Nautilus ahead as his hook remains lane-ending.","Two-plus items flips to you — Chronoshift and speed hard-counter his single-target CC."]},
  {"a":"zilean_sup","b":"neeko","win":["Neeko","Neeko","Neeko","Skill","Neeko","Skill","Zilean"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 2","text":"Neeko out-spikes you at 2: Tangle-Barbs (E) root plus Blooming Burst (Q) is a heavy poke-and-root combo, and if her E catches your stationary body her ADC gets a free trade. Play back, dodge the E line, and don't feed her the level-2 kill window."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"Pop Blossom (R) is a huge AoE stun she can channel from a disguised minion or a flanking Shapesplitter (W) walk-in; you can't dash out, so ward her flank paths, hold Chronoshift, and speed your carry out of the ult radius before it detonates."},{"when":"1st item","text":"Neeko stays ahead through her first item — her burst plus root chain still threatens to delete your ADC in a single combo, and your poke alone can't out-trade that. Keep spacing and respect her disguise roams."},{"when":"Late","text":"By two items you flip it: Chronoshift denies her all-in-or-nothing Pop Blossom combo the kill it's built for, and your speed-ups pull the target out of the stun, wasting her whole burst pattern."}],"wants":{"you":["Dodge Tangle-Barbs (E) — the root is her setup for everything","Speed your ADC out of Pop Blossom (R) radius before it lands","Hold Chronoshift for the target her R+E combo bursts"],"foe":["Land Tangle-Barbs (E) root to chain into Q burst","Use Shapesplitter (W) disguise to walk in unseen for Pop Blossom (R)","Combo R-E-Q to one-shot the ADC through your poke"]},"early":"Levels 1-3 belong to Neeko. Her Blooming Burst plus Tangle-Barbs is a poke-and-root package that punishes your immobility — one E root sets a full trade or a jungle gank. Sit back, sidestep the E skillshot, keep the wave neutral, and only step up to bomb when her root is down.","mid":"Level 4 is a brief even window, but at 6 Neeko surges back: Pop Blossom is a game-ending AoE stun she can hide with her passive clone or Shapesplitter disguise, and her burst combo can delete your carry. Ward her flank routes, track her roams, pre-cast Chronoshift on the likely target, and use Time Warp to yank your ADC out of the ult radius.","late":"Two items flips the lane to you. Chronoshift is the perfect answer to her all-or-nothing burst — you rez the carry she blows Pop Blossom on — and your speed-ups walk the team out of the stun's telegraph. Once her one-combo kill fails, her whole kit falls flat and your scaling utility takes over.","whys":["Level 1 favours Neeko as her poke-and-root combo pressures your immobile body.","Level 2 is Neeko's; E root plus Q sets a strong trade window.","Level 3 stays Neeko's on burst and root threat.","Level 4 is a brief even window before her ult comes online.","Level 6 swings back to Neeko — hidden Pop Blossom threatens a game-ending stun.","First item keeps Neeko ahead as her burst can still delete the ADC.","Two-plus items flips to you — Chronoshift and speed nullify her all-or-nothing combo."]},
  {"a":"zilean_sup","b":"poppy","win":["Zilean","Zilean","Zilean","Zilean","Zilean","Skill","Zilean"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 2","text":"You hit Q-into-Q double-bomb for a huge burst at level 2 while Poppy has no ranged answer; walk up, land the first Q on Poppy or her ADC, and detonate the recast for a chunk she can't heal off minions."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"Chronoshift makes any Poppy W-stop or E-pin all-in fail — she blows her whole combo, kills you, and you rez behind her, so bait the engage and let your ADC clean up while she has nothing left."},{"when":"1st item","text":"With your first component you can double-bomb chunk Poppy off cooldown and out-poke her lane; she has no sustained trade back, only a gap-close she can't reach you with when you're bombing from max range."},{"when":"Late","text":"You keep pace by resetting your ADC or the diving carry with Chronoshift and speeding them out of Poppy's ultimate knock-away, blunting her disengage-and-peel identity in teamfights."}],"wants":{"you":["Poke with Q-Q double bombs from max range so she never trades even","Bait her E-pin and W-shield into your Chronoshift ult","Keep your ADC speed-buffed to dodge her Heroic Charge line"],"foe":["Walk you down with Steadfast Presence speed and E-pin you into a wall","Save W to block your ADC's escape dash during her all-in","Hit her ultimate to peel you and your ADC off her backline"]},"early":"You dominate levels 1-2: Zilean's double-bomb Q burst out-ranges everything Poppy has, and she must eat free poke because her only engage is a short E-charge that needs a wall to stun. Bomb her when she steps up to trade or CS-shove, and back off her W-shield radius.","mid":"Through 3-5 you stay ahead by poking on every Q cooldown and using your E to speed-kite away from her Heroic Charge; she can't answer double bombs, so respect only the wall-pin and keep the lane state in your favor.","late":"At 6 and into items your Chronoshift turns every Poppy all-in against you or your ADC into a wasted combo, and you rescue divers from her ultimate knock-away, so you scale ahead of her utility.","whys":["Zilean's level-1 double-bomb poke out-ranges Poppy's melee kit so you win the first trade.","At level 2 your Q-Q burst chunks her with no ranged trade-back available.","Level 3 you out-poke and can speed-kite her only gap-close.","Through 4-5 sustained bomb damage keeps you ahead of her wall-dependent engage.","At 6 Chronoshift hard-counters her single all-in so the level favors you.","First item is skill: she can look for wall-pin picks if you misposition.","With 2+ items your peel and revive negate her disengage identity, tilting it back to you."]},
  {"a":"zilean_sup","b":"pyke","win":["Skill","Skill","Skill","Skill","Pyke","Pyke","Pyke"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 2","text":"Even window: you can double-bomb Pyke when he steps up to Q-poke, but his Bone Skewer pull and Ghostwater dash let him trade back, so this is a spacing duel decided by who lands first."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"Pyke's Death From Below executes low targets and resets, so any Chronoshift you place is his cue to disengage the marked ally and re-ult someone else; his ult out-tempos your single revive."},{"when":"1st item","text":"Pyke spikes hard on lethality — his hook plus R can one-shot your ADC through your bomb-speed, and he roams with his ult and E to snowball other lanes while you're stuck peeling."},{"when":"Late","text":"Pyke's roam-and-execute pressure and reset ult scale his pick threat above your revive; you must ward deep and pre-shield/speed your carry constantly to survive his all-ins."}],"wants":{"you":["Bomb Pyke when he loads his Q or dashes in so he can't freely poke","Speed your ADC out of his Bone Skewer line with E","Ward his flanks so his invisibility roams don't catch you"],"foe":["Land Bone Skewer to pull you or your ADC into a hook-R kill","Use Death From Below to execute and reset off your low carry","Roam with Ghostwater Dive stealth to snowball other lanes"]},"early":"Levels 1-3 are a skill matchup: your double bombs can punish Pyke's step-up Q-poke, but his Bone Skewer hook and dash-heal let him trade and threaten a pull-kill, so it comes down to who wins the spacing and whether you dodge his skewer.","mid":"Through 4-5 it stays even — you out-poke if he mispositions, he out-picks if you get hooked; keep bombs ready to burst him when he commits and E your ADC out of skewer range.","late":"From 6 on Pyke pulls ahead: Death From Below executes and resets faster than your Chronoshift can trade back, and his lethality picks plus stealth roams outscale your single-target revive unless you ward heavily and pre-empt his all-ins.","whys":["Level 1 is even — your bomb range vs his hook poke is a spacing wash.","Level 2 stays skill: your double-bomb trades against his skewer-dash back.","Level 3 remains even as both look for the first commit.","Through 4-5 neither snowballs cleanly; it's decided by hooks landed.","At 6 Pyke's execute-reset ult out-tempos your single revive, favoring him.","First item his lethality one-shot threat and roams give him the edge.","With 2+ items his pick-and-reset scaling beats your peel, so he stays ahead."]},
  {"a":"zilean_sup","b":"rakan","win":["Skill","Skill","Rakan","Rakan","Rakan","Rakan","Skill"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 2","text":"Even: you can double-bomb Rakan when he steps in for a W-charge, but his Gleaming Quill poke and shield keep him healthy, so respect his engage range and only commit bombs when his W is down."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"Rakan's Grand Entrance plus R Battle Dance make him a slippery multi-target engage; your Chronoshift saves the one target he all-ins, but he simply dashes back out and re-engages, so his mobility out-tempos your peel window."},{"when":"1st item","text":"Rakan spikes as an engage-disengage machine — W knock-up into R charm can lock your ADC before your bomb-speed matters, and his dashes let him pick your backline and escape your follow-up."},{"when":"Late","text":"Even lategame: your Chronoshift and speed-buffs can undo his engage kills and let your carry survive the charm chain, matching his playmaking so teamfights come down to who lands their setup first."}],"wants":{"you":["Bomb Rakan when his W or R dash is on cooldown so he can't shrug it off","Speed your ADC out of his Grand Entrance and R charm line","Pre-place Chronoshift on your carry before he commits his engage"],"foe":["Land Grand Entrance W knock-up to start a charm-R all-in","Use Battle Dance dashes to pick your backline and escape","Shield-poke with Gleaming Quill to win the sustain trade"]},"early":"Levels 1-2 play even: Zilean's double-bomb can punish Rakan when he walks up to W-engage, but his Quill heal and shield let him sustain the poke war, so it's a spacing skill duel where you watch his engage cooldowns.","mid":"Through 3-5 Rakan edges ahead — his W knock-up into charm gives him a reliable all-in that beats your single-target revive on the initiation, and his dash mobility lets him pick and escape faster than you can punish, so hold Chronoshift and speed to survive rather than trade.","late":"By the time you both have ults and items it evens out: Chronoshift plus your E speed can nullify the target he engages and get your ADC out of the charm chain, so fights hinge on execution — you peel, he playmakers, and whoever lands first wins.","whys":["Level 1 is even — your bomb poke trades against his shield-heal sustain.","Level 2 stays skill as you punish his W step-in but he heals it back.","Level 3 Rakan's W-into-charm all-in threat tips the lane his way.","Through 4-5 his engage mobility out-tempos your single revive.","At 6 his multi-dash R engage still out-paces your peel window.","First item his pick-and-escape playmaking keeps him ahead.","With 2+ items your revive and speed match his engage, evening it back out."]},
  {"a":"zilean_sup","b":"rell","win":["Zilean","Skill","Rell","Rell","Rell","Rell","Zilean"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 2","text":"Even at 2: your double-bomb out-ranges Rell, but her W dismount crash and E-bind threaten a hard engage, so bomb her when she steps up and back out of her mount-crash range."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"Rell's Magnet Storm ult pulls everyone in and her W crash is a long-range engage; Chronoshift saves the one target she flattens, but her AoE lockdown lets her ADC clean up before your revive matters."},{"when":"1st item","text":"Rell spikes as a tank engage — her dismount W plus E stun lock your ADC in place, and your bomb-speed can't kite out of the AoE, so she dictates every all-in in her favor."},{"when":"Late","text":"Late you claw it back: Chronoshift undoes the kill her engage sets up and your E speed can pull your carry out of Magnet Storm, so your peel matches her lockdown when fights go long."}],"wants":{"you":["Bomb Rell at range before she can dismount-crash onto you","Speed your ADC out of her W crash and E stun with E","Save Chronoshift for the target she flattens with her engage"],"foe":["Land the W dismount crash to start a stun-chain all-in","Bind your ADC with E Attract and Repel to lock the kill","Ult Magnet Storm to drag your whole backline into her ADC"]},"early":"Level 1 favors you — Zilean's double-bomb poke out-ranges Rell's melee mounted form and she has no way to trade back before her W is up. At 2 it evens as her dismount crash and E-bind come online and threaten a hard engage, so poke her down but respect the crash range.","mid":"Through 3-5 Rell takes over: her W crash plus E stun is a reliable point-and-click all-in that your bomb-speed can't kite out of, so you shift to holding Chronoshift and speed to survive rather than win trades, and ward her flanks for the engage.","late":"With ults and items you swing it back — Chronoshift reverses the kill her lockdown creates and your E speed drags your carry out of Magnet Storm, so your revive-and-peel package matches her AoE engage when fights go long.","whys":["Level 1 your ranged double-bomb out-pokes her melee mount, favoring you.","Level 2 evens as her dismount-crash and E-bind engage come online.","Level 3 Rell's reliable W-E all-in outmuscles your single revive.","Through 4-5 her point-blank lockdown beats your kite, favoring her.","At 6 Magnet Storm's AoE pull lets her team collapse before you rez.","First item her tanky engage still dictates every all-in.","With 2+ items your Chronoshift and speed match her lockdown, tilting it back to you."]},
  {"a":"zilean_sup","b":"renata","win":["Skill","Skill","Skill","Skill","Skill","Skill","Skill"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 2","text":"Even: your double-bomb can chunk Renata when she steps up, but her Handshake root-toss and W Bailout make her hard to punish, so trade bombs when her Q is down and respect the pull."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"Renata's Hostile Takeover berserks your team while your Chronoshift saves one ally — both are game-changing ults, so fights hinge on whether her R turns a carry before your revive lands, a true skill window."},{"when":"1st item","text":"Both of you are utility enchanters now: her Handshake pick and Bailout save trade evenly against your bombs and revive, so lane is decided by who lands their key spell, not by raw stats."},{"when":"Late","text":"Even scaling: your Chronoshift and speed answer her Bailout revive-buff and R berserk one-for-one, so teamfights come down to positioning and who commits their ultimate first."}],"wants":{"you":["Bomb Renata when her Handshake Q is on cooldown","Speed your ADC out of her Handshake pull line with E","Pre-place Chronoshift to counter her Hostile Takeover flip"],"foe":["Land Handshake to pull your carry and start a pick","Use Bailout to bait your all-in then reverse the trade","Ult Hostile Takeover to turn your ADC against your team"]},"early":"Levels 1-3 are a pure skill matchup between two utility supports: your double-bomb poke threatens Renata when she steps up, but her Handshake pull and Bailout save let her trade back and punish overextension, so it's about dodging her Q and spacing your bombs.","mid":"Through 4-5 it stays even — neither of you brings hard lane-ending burst, so the lane is a poke-and-utility standoff decided by who lands their key ability and coordinates the all-in with their ADC.","late":"With ults online it remains a skill fight: her Hostile Takeover berserk and Bailout answer your Chronoshift revive and speed one-for-one, so teamfights come down to positioning and ultimate timing rather than a kit advantage.","whys":["Level 1 is even — bomb poke vs her pull-and-save utility is a wash.","Level 2 stays skill as your double-bomb trades against her Handshake threat.","Level 3 neither gains an edge; it's a spacing duel.","Through 4-5 both lack lane-ending burst so it stays even.","At 6 both ults are game-changing, so the R timing decides fights evenly.","First item both are utility enchanters trading one-for-one.","With 2+ items your revive-speed and her berserk-save scale evenly."]},
  {"a":"zilean_sup","b":"senna","win":["Senna","Senna","Senna","Skill","Skill","Skill","Senna"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 2","text":"Senna out-ranges you early — her Piercing Darkness Q pokes and heals through minions from way outside your bomb range, so she chips you down while you struggle to land Q without walking into her auto-crit range."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"Even-ish: her Dawning Shadow global shield-or-nuke rivals your Chronoshift as a fight-swinger, but you can revive the target she snipes, so the ult trade is close and comes down to timing."},{"when":"1st item","text":"Senna scales harder — her stacking Q gives her range, crit, and lifesteal that outpaces your poke, and her root-Q plus black mist stealth let her pick while healing, so she dictates the trades."},{"when":"Late","text":"Senna's global ult, long-range roots, and hypercarry stacking outscale your single-target utility; you counter by reviving her snipe targets and speeding allies out of her Q root, but she holds the lane edge."}],"wants":{"you":["Bomb Senna when she steps up to Q-poke or auto for a stack","Speed your ADC out of her Piercing Darkness root line","Revive the carry she snipes with Dawning Shadow"],"foe":["Poke-heal with Piercing Darkness from max range through minions","Root you with the enemy-hit portion of her Q to set a pick","Stack Q relentlessly to outrange and outscale your bombs"]},"early":"Senna owns levels 1-3: her Piercing Darkness Q out-ranges your double-bomb and heals her through the trade, so she pokes you down for free while stacking, and her auto-crit passive punishes you if you step into bomb range. Play safe, poke only when her Q is down, and don't feed her stacks by trading into her range.","mid":"Through 4-5 it evens slightly as your bombs come online and you can burst her when she mispositions, but she still out-ranges and out-sustains you, so hold Chronoshift and speed to survive her poke rather than force trades.","late":"Senna pulls ahead again with items and stacks — her global Dawning Shadow, long-range roots, and crit-lifesteal scaling outpace your single-target revive, so you play reactive: rez her snipe targets, E allies out of her root, and let your ADC out-scale hers.","whys":["Level 1 Senna's Q out-ranges and out-heals your bombs, favoring her.","Level 2 she keeps poking and stacking beyond your reach.","Level 3 her range and sustain still dominate the poke war.","Through 4-5 your bombs online it up so trades even out.","At 6 your Chronoshift revive answers her global ult, keeping it even.","First item is skill as you can still punish her missteps.","With 2+ items her stacking hypercarry scaling outpaces your utility, favoring her."]},
  {"a":"zilean_sup","b":"seraphine","win":["Skill","Skill","Skill","Skill","Skill","Skill","Skill"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 2","text":"Hit level 2 first and you can Q-W-Q double-bomb Seraphine for a stun as she steps up to last-hit or land Sound of Celerity poke; she has no dash, so a stun start is your cleanest kill window."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"Chronoshift neutralizes her Encore ult: even if she charms you both and her ADC dumps damage, you revive the priority target and turn her big cooldown into a wasted fight."},{"when":"1st item","text":"Even breakpoint; your Rod/tear tempo matches her Lost Chapter, so whoever manages mana and dodges skillshots takes the poke lead."},{"when":"Late","text":"Both of you are heavy AoE enablers; the fight tips on execution, with your double-bomb burst and revive trading blows against her stacked-note shields and Encore."}],"wants":{"you":["Land the level-2 double-bomb stun before she gets W shields online","Bank Chronoshift for whoever her Encore charm chains onto","Use Time Warp slow to stick your ADC onto her once she's grouped up"],"foe":["Poke you down with echoed Q notes so you can't afford to trade","Land Encore charm on two targets to snowball a fight","Shield-and-heal through your bombs with a passive-note W"]},"early":"Even lane at 1-2: both of you are immobile spellcasters trading skillshots, so the level-2 timing decides the first window. If you get W before she gets her shield, a Q-Rewind-Q stun into your ADC's follow-up is a real kill; if she spaces well and echoes Q pokes, she chips you instead.","mid":"From 3 to 6 it stays a coin-flip poke war. You out-burst her single target with double bombs, she out-sustains a slow grind with W shields and passive-note heals, so target the lower-mobility of her and her ADC and force short trades where your stun lands.","late":"At items and beyond neither support wins on paper; it's a skill fight. Your Chronoshift hard-counters her Encore teamfight windows while your Time Warp peels or engages, and she answers with layered shields and AoE charm, so cleaner combos win.","whys":["Both are immobile poke supports with no early edge, so level 1 is a skill matchup.","Your level-2 double-bomb and her level-2 poke roughly cancel, leaving it even.","Neither spikes hard at 3; it's still a symmetric skillshot poke trade.","At 4-5 your burst and her sustain stay balanced, so it comes down to dodging.","Chronoshift and Encore are mirror-value ult windows, keeping level 6 even.","First-item power spikes arrive together, so the poke lead is skill-decided.","Two AoE enablers scale in parallel, so late fights hinge on execution not the matchup."]},
  {"a":"zilean_sup","b":"sona","win":["Skill","Skill","Skill","Zilean","Skill","Skill","Skill"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 2","text":"Level-2 double-bomb is your best kill button since Sona is squishy and dashless, but her W shield and Aria heals can absorb a sloppy single bomb, so land the Q-Rewind-Q stun cleanly."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"Crescendo is a point-and-click AoE stun that headlines her all-in; you can't dodge it, so hold Chronoshift to revive whoever it locks up rather than trying to out-trade the ult window."},{"when":"1st item","text":"She hits her Q-poke item tempo (tear/Archangel path) right as you do, so the free-poke advantage evens back out after your level 4-5 spike."},{"when":"Late","text":"Both scale as enablers; her Power Chord empowerments and Crescendo trade against your double-bomb burst and revive, leaving fights on positioning."}],"wants":{"you":["Spike at 4-5 when you have full double-bomb mana and Time Warp to all-in her","Bank Chronoshift for the Crescendo target","Punish her short Q range by bombing her when she steps up to poke"],"foe":["Poke you with double-cast Q from max range behind her ADC","Land Crescendo on both of you to open a guaranteed all-in","Shield and speed her ADC out of your bomb range with W and E"]},"early":"Roughly even at 1-3: Sona pokes with double Power Chord-charged Q but has paper-thin health and no escape, so any clean level-2 stun threatens her hard while her shields threaten to blank a lone bomb. Respect that she out-ranges your auto poke and trades with W up.","mid":"Level 4-5 is your window: with maxed Time Bomb and enough mana for a Q-Rewind-Q chain plus Time Warp, you can burst her before her sustain matters and she has no dash to escape the stun. Force the all-in here before her level-6 Crescendo comes online.","late":"From 6 onward it flattens to a skill fight; her Crescendo is an unmissable teamfight stun you answer with Chronoshift rather than dodging, and both of you scale as pure enablers. Whoever lands their AoE and protects the right carry wins the exchange.","whys":["Both are immobile casters at level 1, so no one holds an edge.","Level-2 stun and her poke roughly trade, keeping it even.","At 3 her sustain matches your poke, so it stays a skill matchup.","At 4-5 your maxed double-bomb burst beats her sustain on a dashless target, favoring you.","Crescendo is an undodgeable ult that levels the fight back to even at 6.","Her poke-item tempo arrives with yours, so first item is skill-decided.","Two scaling enablers trade evenly late, leaving fights on positioning."]},
  {"a":"zilean_sup","b":"soraka","win":["Skill","Skill","Skill","Skill","Skill","Skill","Skill"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 2","text":"Level-2 double-bomb is your only real burst threat; Soraka is immobile and squishy, so a Q-Rewind-Q stun into your ADC can spike her before her heals matter, but a single bomb just gets Astral Infusion'd back."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"Her ult is a global heal, not a fight-changer in lane; your Chronoshift is the stronger 2v2 tool, but neither ult creates a kill by itself so the window stays even."},{"when":"1st item","text":"You both spike into mana-and-poke items at once; her Q silence-slow zoning matches your bomb range, so the sustain-versus-poke grind stays balanced."},{"when":"Late","text":"Pure enabler mirror: her chain heals and Equinox root trade against your double-bomb burst and revive, so team positioning decides fights, not the lane."}],"wants":{"you":["Burst her below her Astral Infusion self-heal threshold with a full double-bomb combo","Force short all-ins so she can't chain heals to full","Slow her ADC with Time Warp so your carry sticks damage on"],"foe":["Out-sustain your poke with Starcall stacks and Astral Infusion","Zone you off with Equinox silence when you step up to bomb","Heal her ADC through your all-in so trades net her tempo"]},"early":"Even and slow at 1-3: Soraka wants a passive poke-and-heal grind while you look for the level-2 double-bomb stun. She has no dash and pays health to heal, so a clean burst all-in punishes her, but a single uncoordinated bomb is trivially healed back by Astral Infusion.","mid":"From 3 to 6 it's a sustain-versus-burst standoff. You can't win a slow poke war against infinite heals, so you have to commit hard all-ins with a stun and your ADC's damage to push her below the point where healing you both is worth it, while dodging her Q slow and Equinox silence.","late":"At items and beyond it's a skill matchup between two enablers. Her heal output and Equinox answer your double-bomb burst and Chronoshift revive, so whoever's team positions better and forces the fight on their terms wins; the lane itself gives no lasting edge.","whys":["Two immobile supports at level 1 means no early edge, purely skill.","Level-2 stun and her heal-sustain cancel, keeping it even.","At 3 her heals match your poke, so it stays skill-decided.","At 4-5 burst and sustain stay balanced, hinging on all-in execution.","Neither ult wins lane 2v2, so level 6 is even.","Poke and mana items arrive together, leaving first item a skill matchup.","Two scaling enablers trade evenly, so late fights turn on positioning."]},
  {"a":"zilean_sup","b":"swain","win":["Swain","Swain","Swain","Swain","Swain","Swain","Zilean"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 2","text":"Swain's level-2 spike beats yours: his double-bolt Q out-ranges your poke and his Nevermove (E) or Vision of Empire (W) root can lock you for a full bomb-less trade, so don't contest the level-2 all-in."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"Demonic Ascension gives him a burst of drain-tank sustain and, with his pull, a strong 2v2 all-in; your Chronoshift can revive through it but you're still on the back foot in the fight."},{"when":"1st item","text":"His first-item tempo makes him a lane bully with soul-fragment heals and constant Q poke, out-trading your single-target bombs before your scaling kicks in."},{"when":"Late","text":"At 2+ items you flip it: double-bomb one-shots and a guaranteed Chronoshift out-value his drain tanking, and Time Warp lets you kite his rooted engages."}],"wants":{"you":["Survive the early poke phase and scale to your 2+ item spike","Dodge Nevermove and Vision of Empire so he can't land a free root-into-Q","Peel his all-in with Chronoshift and Time Warp once teamfights start"],"foe":["Bully you with double-bolt Q poke and soul-fragment sustain","Land E or W root to chain a full damage rotation onto you","All-in under Demonic Ascension while he out-sustains your bombs"]},"early":"Swain owns levels 1-3: his Q hits twice at longer range than your poke, his passive heals off soul fragments, and either of his roots turns a step-up into a free trade you can't answer. Play back, dodge his skillshots, and don't try to contest the poke war head-on because you lose it.","mid":"From 4 to 6 he stays ahead as a lane bully; maxed Q and his root threat let him zone you off CS and poke your ADC, and at 6 Demonic Ascension adds sustain and all-in pressure. Your job is to farm safely, bank Chronoshift, and avoid feeding his soul-fragment stacks until your items come online.","late":"At 2+ items the matchup flips to you: double Time Bombs delete his backline value, Chronoshift denies his all-in payoff, and Time Warp both peels his rooted engage and speeds your carry out of his ult range. Out-scale him and the earlier lane deficit stops mattering.","whys":["Swain's longer double-Q range and root give him the level-1 edge.","At level 2 his poke and root beat your double-bomb window, favoring him.","His maxed Q and sustain keep the poke war his at level 3.","At 4-5 his zoning and soul-fragment heals still out-trade you.","Demonic Ascension's sustain and all-in tilt level 6 to Swain.","First-item bully tempo keeps him ahead before your scaling.","At 2+ items your burst and revive out-value his drain tank, flipping it to you."]},
  {"a":"zilean_sup","b":"tahmkench","win":["Skill","Skill","Skill","Skill","Skill","Skill","Zilean"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 2","text":"Level-2 double-bomb threatens him, but Tahm's gray-health passive and shield (E) soak burst well, so you need the Q-Rewind-Q stun plus your ADC to actually punish rather than a lone bomb."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"His R Devour can save his ADC from your all-in or reposition to eat your carry; hold Chronoshift for the target he dives, since neither ult cleanly wins the 2v2 by itself."},{"when":"1st item","text":"Even tempo: his Q slow-into-stun on three stacks matches your bomb poke, so whoever lands their skillshots and avoids the tongue takes the lane lead."},{"when":"Late","text":"You out-scale him at 2+ items: double-bomb burst can blow up a target faster than he can Devour-save it, and Chronoshift plus Time Warp answer his engage and peel."}],"wants":{"you":["Scale to your 2+ item double-bomb spike where you out-value his saves","Dodge his Q tongue so he can't land the three-stack stun engage","Bank Chronoshift for whoever he tries to Devour or dive"],"foe":["Land Tongue Lash to slow you into a stun-stack engage","Devour his ADC out of your bomb combo to blank your all-in","Soak your poke with gray health and E shield, then all-in on cooldown"]},"early":"Even and grindy at 1-3: Tahm pokes and threatens the Q tongue that, on three stacks, becomes a stun engage, while you look for your level-2 double-bomb. His gray health and shield make him hard to burst, so trades stay short and skill-based; the whole lane hinges on whether you eat his tongue.","mid":"From 4 to 6 it stays even. He's tanky and hard to kill outright, so your poke chips but rarely converts, and his engage is scary only if the Q connects. Play around his tongue cooldown, keep your ADC out of stun range, and don't over-commit a bomb combo he can shrug with W gray health.","late":"At 2+ items you take over: double Time Bombs burst a target faster than his Devour can react, Chronoshift denies the save-and-dive he's built around, and Time Warp peels his engage or speeds your carry clear. His utility tanking can't keep pace with your scaling enabler kit.","whys":["Both open safely with no early kill pressure, so level 1 is even.","Level-2 stun and his tanky trades cancel, keeping it skill-decided.","At 3 his gray-health durability matches your poke, staying even.","At 4-5 your burst and his saves balance out, hinging on the tongue.","Neither ult wins the 2v2 alone, so level 6 stays even.","First-item poke and his stun engage trade evenly, skill-decided.","At 2+ items your double-bomb burst and revive out-scale his tanking, favoring you."]},
  {"a":"zilean_sup","b":"taric","win":["Skill","Skill","Skill","Skill","Taric","Taric","Taric"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 2","text":"Your level-2 double-bomb is a real kill threat since Taric is slow and dashless before he has stacks; land the Q-Rewind-Q stun into your ADC before his Bastion shields and passive heals stabilize him."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"Cosmic Radiance is the problem: after a delay it makes him and his ADC invulnerable, blanking your entire double-bomb burst, so his ult swings the 2v2 harder than your Chronoshift here."},{"when":"1st item","text":"His tank-support item tempo plus Bastion-linked E stun make his all-in more reliable than your poke, so the extended-fight edge tips to him."},{"when":"Late","text":"In drawn-out fights his Bastion peel, long E stun, and Cosmic Radiance invuln out-value your burst; you win by poking before the fight, not trading inside his ult window."}],"wants":{"you":["Cash your early poke and level-2 burst lead before his ult and stacks come online","Force short trades and back off before his Bastion E stun links","Poke him and his ADC down out of combat where Cosmic Radiance can't save them"],"foe":["Reach level 6 and use Cosmic Radiance to invuln through your all-in","Land the Bastion-doubled E stun to lock your ADC in a fight","Grind extended fights where his peel and heals beat your burst"]},"early":"Even and skill-based at 1-4, tilting on your burst windows: Taric is immobile with a slow E stun that needs a Bastion link or an auto to prime, so your level-2 double-bomb stun genuinely threatens him before he's tanky. Chip him and his ADC with poke, but respect that his shields and heals stabilize any trade you don't fully commit.","mid":"Through levels 3-5 it stays a skill fight where your poke lead matters, but the moment he hits 6 it turns his way. Cosmic Radiance's delayed invulnerability blanks your double-bomb all-in entirely, so stop trying to burst inside his ult and instead force your damage out before the fight starts.","late":"At items and beyond Taric's teamfight tools win extended exchanges: his long E stun, Bastion peel on his carry, and the invuln ult neutralize your burst-and-revive pattern. Your path to the overall lead is poking both of them down in the vision game and picking fights when Cosmic Radiance is on cooldown, not trading inside it.","whys":["Both immobile at level 1 with no dash, so it's an even skill start.","Your level-2 burst and his shield-heal stabilization roughly cancel, staying even.","At 3 his sustain matches your poke, keeping it skill-decided.","At 4-5 your poke and his durability balance, hinging on your burst windows.","Cosmic Radiance's invuln blanks your all-in, swinging level 6 to Taric.","His tank tempo and Bastion E stun make his all-in more reliable at first item.","In extended fights his peel, stun, and invuln out-value your burst, favoring Taric."]},
  {"a":"zilean_sup","b":"thresh","win":["Skill","Thresh","Thresh","Thresh","Thresh","Thresh","Zilean"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 2","text":"Thresh spikes harder at 2: his Q hook plus E Flay is a point-and-click all-in, while your second point is just a second Q bomb or an early E slow. Hold your Q double-bomb stun for the moment he Flays your ADC so you cancel the follow-up, and never facecheck a brush he could be hiding in for a Death Sentence."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"Both ults are defensive-flavored here, but Thresh keeps lane priority: his Q, W lantern, and E all pressure while your Chronoshift only matters if you already committed. Pre-place a bomb on yourself or your ADC before any trade so the stun is up to peel a hook, and use Rewind aggressively to keep a stun charged during his hook cooldown."},{"when":"1st item","text":"Thresh's hook still dictates the lane on one item, and his flat scaling means he stays a threat, but your double-bomb E slow and Chronoshift start swinging skirmishes your way. Track his Q cooldown (~18-20s early) and step up only in that window."},{"when":"Late","text":"Zilean pulls ahead with items: Chronoshift plus your global speed and a full double-bomb combo makes any Thresh hook a non-lethal pick, since you rez the caught target. Your teamfight peel and pick-recovery outscale his single-target lockdown."}],"wants":{"you":["Punish his Q cooldown windows to poke with bombs","Keep a stun charge banked via Rewind to cancel Flay engages","Reach two items so Chronoshift neutralizes his hook picks"],"foe":["Land a blind Death Sentence in brush before you can bank a stun","Chain Q into E Flay to burst your ADC at level 2","Bait your Chronoshift then re-engage on the timer"]},"early":"Level 1 is even skill expression, but the moment Thresh hits 2 his Q-into-Flay all-in outguns your single bomb, so respect brush and never walk up without a stun ready.","mid":"Levels 3 through 5 belong to Thresh: his hook, lantern peel, and Flay give him constant kill threat while you're forced to hold your double-bomb stun purely reactively to cancel his engage.","late":"On items and past two completed, Zilean flips it: Chronoshift and your global speed turn his hook picks into failed engages, and your peel outscales his single-target lockdown.","whys":["Level 1 is a skill-even standoff since neither of you can force a kill with one ability.","Thresh spikes at 2 because Q hook into E Flay is a guaranteed all-in your single point can't match.","At 3 his full hook-lantern-Flay kit keeps kill pressure you can only react to.","Through levels 4-5 Thresh's cooldowns stay low enough to threaten picks every wave.","At 6 his engage still dictates trades while your Chronoshift is purely reactive.","On first item Thresh's flat hook scaling keeps him the lane threat.","With two-plus items Zilean's Chronoshift and speed neutralize hook picks and pull ahead."]},
  {"a":"zilean_sup","b":"velkoz","win":["Skill","Skill","Vel'Koz","Vel'Koz","Vel'Koz","Vel'Koz","Zilean"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 2","text":"Early levels are a poke race and it's close, but Vel'Koz's Q split and W plasma out-range your single bomb. Use your bombs to farm-poke from max range and immediately Rewind for a second bomb, and dodge his Q by moving perpendicular the instant it fires since it splits on a re-cast."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"Vel'Koz's R channel is the whole lane's threat: if you eat sustained W-Q-E Deconstruction stacks his ult can nearly delete your ADC. Pre-place a double-bomb stun on your carry so if Vel'Koz E-knocks up to set up combos you can peel, and save Chronoshift to rez through his ult burst."},{"when":"1st item","text":"Vel'Koz out-pokes you on first item thanks to his three damage abilities versus your two, and his true-damage passive chunks your sustain. Ward the flanks, walk up only behind minions, and use your speed to juke his slow-traveling W."},{"when":"Late","text":"Zilean scales past him: Chronoshift plus your double-bomb stun turns his immobile long-channel ult into a liability, since you can stun him out of it or rez the target he bursts. Your team's engage on a stationary Vel'Koz is a free kill you enable."}],"wants":{"you":["Bank a second bomb with Rewind to win poke exchanges","Pre-place your stun to peel his E knock-up combos","Reach two items so Chronoshift and stun punish his ult channel"],"foe":["Chain Q-W-E to stack Deconstruction true damage on you","Land his E to set up a full R burst on your ADC","Zone you off farm with superior W plasma range"]},"early":"The first two levels are a skill-based poke race; his Q and W out-range your bomb but a well-timed Rewind double-bomb keeps you even if you dodge his splits.","mid":"Levels 3 through 6 Vel'Koz takes over the poke war with three damage abilities and true-damage stacks, forcing you to farm cautiously behind minions and hold your stun for his E setups.","late":"By two items Zilean wins: your double-bomb stun interrupts his channel and Chronoshift rezzes anyone his ult bursts, turning his immobility into your team's free pick.","whys":["Level 1 is skill-even as both trade single spells at range.","Level 2 stays even since your Rewind double-bomb answers his early poke.","At 3 Vel'Koz's Q-W poke range starts out-trading your bombs.","Through 4-5 his three-ability poke and true-damage passive grind you down.","At 6 his R channel is the dominant lane-wide burst threat.","On first item his poke superiority and passive keep you on the back foot.","With two-plus items Zilean's stun and Chronoshift punish his immobile ult and flip the matchup."]},
  {"a":"zilean_sup","b":"xerath","win":["Skill","Skill","Xerath","Xerath","Xerath","Xerath","Zilean"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 2","text":"The opening levels are an even artillery duel, but Xerath's Q charge out-ranges your bomb and his W is an AoE zone. Trade with a bomb then Rewind for a second, and side-step his Q on release since it has a fixed cast point you can read from the charge animation."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"Xerath's R gives him three long-range global shots that punish anyone standing still, and his E stun sets them up. Keep a double-bomb stun banked to cancel his E-into-R combo on your ADC, and use Chronoshift to rez through his ult barrage rather than blowing it early."},{"when":"1st item","text":"With mana and range items Xerath dominates the poke war from a screen away, chunking you before you can retaliate. Hug minions to block his Q, ward river so his E can't catch you stepping up, and let your ADC farm safely under tower."},{"when":"Late","text":"Zilean outscales the artillery: your double-bomb stun and Chronoshift make his immobile, channel-reliant R low-value, and your speed lets you close the gap or peel the moment he lands E. A stationary Xerath is a free engage for your team."}],"wants":{"you":["Rewind a second bomb to match his poke cadence","Bank your stun to interrupt his E-into-R setup","Reach two items so Chronoshift devalues his artillery burst"],"foe":["Zone you off farm with screen-range Q poke","Land E to guarantee a charged Q and R follow-up","Chip you below Chronoshift value before a fight starts"]},"early":"Levels 1-2 are an even long-range trade; his Q out-ranges your bomb but Rewind lets you answer, so dodge his fixed cast points and you stay level.","mid":"From 3 through 6 Xerath owns the poke lane with superior range and his E stun setting up big Q and R hits, forcing you to farm behind minions and hold your stun reactively.","late":"By two items Zilean wins out: your stun cancels his combos and Chronoshift rezzes his burst targets, so his immobile artillery becomes your team's engage bait.","whys":["Level 1 is a skill-even artillery standoff.","Level 2 stays even as your Rewind double-bomb matches his early poke.","At 3 Xerath's superior Q range starts out-poking your bombs.","Through 4-5 his range plus E stun setups zone you off farm.","At 6 his global R barrage is the lane's dominant threat.","On first item his mana and range let him poke you from a screen away.","With two-plus items Zilean's stun and Chronoshift neutralize his immobile ult and flip it."]},
  {"a":"zilean_sup","b":"yuumi","win":["Skill","Skill","Skill","Zilean","Zilean","Zilean","Skill"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 2","text":"Yuumi contributes almost nothing to a level-2 all-in beyond a Q poke and a heal, so this is your window: land a bomb on her ADC and Rewind for a second to threaten the stun. Play for the kill on the carry while she's untethered, since when she's attached you can't touch her."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"This is your spike, not hers: her R gives sustain and a slow but no lockdown, while your double-bomb stun plus Chronoshift lets you all-in her ADC and rez your own if it goes long. Bomb the carry, stun it, and force the fight before her heals out-value your burst."},{"when":"1st item","text":"You stay ahead on first item: Zilean's roam speed and bomb pressure let you punish the immobile Yuumi-ADC duo, and she has no way to peel a hard engage from your team. Roam with your speed on her missing timers and force plays before she scales her enchant."},{"when":"Late","text":"Yuumi's scaling heals and shields catch up late, and once her ADC is fed her attach-sustain outvalues your single-target stun in a drawn-out fight. Look to burst her carry fast with a bomb-stun combo before her per-second healing takes over the teamfight."}],"wants":{"you":["All-in her ADC at 2 and 6 while she can't peel","Use your speed to roam on her missing timers","Force short fights before her sustained heals stack up"],"foe":["Attach and out-sustain your poke through the laning phase","Scale her enchant items to heal her ADC through your burst","Drag fights long so her per-second healing outvalues your stun"]},"early":"The first two levels are skill-even farm, but by 3 you start winning: Yuumi adds little to an all-in, so bank a stun and threaten her ADC whenever she's untethered.","mid":"Levels 4 through 6 are your peak; your bomb-stun all-in plus Chronoshift overpowers her no-lockdown kit, so force fights on her carry before her heals scale.","late":"Yuumi's stacking heals and shields even it back to skill late, so kill her ADC fast with a bomb-stun combo before her per-second sustain takes over drawn-out fights.","whys":["Level 1 is even farm as neither side commits.","Level 2 stays skill-even before your all-in windows open.","At 3 it's still close as she can attach and sustain your early poke.","At 4-5 Zilean leads since your bomb-stun all-in beats her no-peel kit.","At 6 your double-bomb stun and Chronoshift outmuscle her lockdown-less ult.","On first item your roam speed and engage keep the immobile duo pinned.","With two-plus items her scaling heals catch up and even the matchup back to skill."]},
  {"a":"zilean_sup","b":"zyra","win":["Skill","Skill","Zyra","Zyra","Zyra","Zyra","Zyra"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 2","text":"The first two levels are close, but Zyra's plant-backed Q and E out-DPS your single bomb in a sustained trade. Poke with a bomb then Rewind for a second and back off before her seeds sprout, and never sit in a lane bush she can E-snare you from."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"Zyra's R is a massive knock-up-then-DPS zone that, combined with her E root and plants, can lock and delete your ADC in a fight. Hold a double-bomb stun to peel the moment she E-roots, and save Chronoshift to rez a target caught by her ult rather than trading it into poke."},{"when":"1st item","text":"Zyra out-damages you on first item; her plants scale with AP so every trade favors her, and her E snare guarantees follow-up burst. Ward the flanking bushes, walk up only behind minions, and use your speed to leave her ult zone before the plants ramp."},{"when":"Late","text":"Zyra stays ahead into items: her AoE root plus ult zone plus enhanced plants deal more teamfight damage than your single-target stun can shut off, and she punishes any grouped positioning. Play spread, use Chronoshift on your carry, and try to burst her before she lands E."}],"wants":{"you":["Bank a Rewind double-bomb before her seeds sprout","Hold your stun to peel her E snare in fights","Use speed and Chronoshift to survive her ult zone"],"foe":["Snare you with E to chain plant-backed burst","Ramp plant DPS in extended trades and fights","Catch grouped targets in her R knock-up zone"]},"early":"Levels 1-2 are a near-even poke trade, but her plant-backed Q and E out-sustain your single bomb, so Rewind a second bomb and retreat before her seeds sprout.","mid":"From 3 onward Zyra takes the lane: her E snare plus scaling plants and AP damage out-trade you, forcing you to farm behind minions and hold your stun purely to peel her root.","late":"Zyra keeps the edge into items; her AoE root, ult zone, and enhanced plants out-damage your single-target stun in fights, so spread out, Chronoshift your carry, and burst her before she lands E.","whys":["Level 1 is a skill-even poke standoff.","Level 2 stays close before her plants ramp.","At 3 Zyra's plant-backed Q-E out-trades your single bomb.","Through 4-5 her E snare and scaling plants control the lane.","At 6 her R knock-up-and-DPS zone is the dominant fight threat.","On first item her AP plant damage out-poke keeps you pinned.","With two-plus items her AoE root and ult zone outdamage your single-target stun and stay ahead."]}
